                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.617,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Kagan has the opinion this morning in Case 13-1074, United States v. Wong and 13-1075, United States v. June."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 11.617,
                        "stop": 190.798,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15094,
                            "name": "Elena Kagan",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/elena_kagan",
                            "last_name": "Kagan",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2738,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1281157200,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Barack Obama",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2738"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32690,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 44456,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/elena-kagan-photo_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 1931,
                            "identifier": "elena_kagan"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 11.617,
                                "stop": 21.365,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Federal Tort Claims Act or FTCA allows individuals who have been injured by federal employees to sue the United States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 21.365,
                                "stop": 28.532,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "And like most statutes authorizing lawsuits, it sets deadlines for when those cases may be brought."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 28.532,
                                "stop": 40.126,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "A person first has to present her claim to a federal agency within two years, and if the agency denies the claim, the person must then bring it to court within six months."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.126,
                                "stop": 44.078,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "If not, the statute says the claim is barred."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 44.078,
                                "stop": 55.721,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The respondents in these cases, Kwai Fun Wong and Marlene June, each missed one of those deadlines when trying to bring a tort claim against the federal government."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.721,
                                "stop": 65.16,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The issue we address today is whether a court can still hear Wong\u0027s and June\u0027s cases if their lateness was not their fault."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.16,
                                "stop": 76.098,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We think the answer is yes under a doctrine known as equitable tolling, which allows Courts to extend statutory deadlines when it\u0027s fair to do so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.098,
                                "stop": 83.685,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This Court long ago established a background presumption that equitable tolling is available in suits against the government."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 83.685,
                                "stop": 93.252,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In other words, as in most other kinds of cases, a person can be excused for failing to meet a time limit if there is very good reason to do so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.252,
                                "stop": 96.662,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But the Court made clear that this presumption is rebuttable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 96.662,
                                "stop": 102.347,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "If Congress wants to make a deadline absolutely unmovable, it can do that."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.347,
                                "stop": 108.812,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "And we have held that one way Congress can express that intent is by making a time limit jurisdictional."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 108.812,
                                "stop": 116.577,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "When Congress does that, it deprives the Court of all authority to hear a late suit, no matter what the circumstance is."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.577,
                                "stop": 128.836,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But because such a rule can have very harsh consequences, we won\u0027t treat a time bar as jurisdictional unless Congress tells us in no uncertain terms that that\u0027s what it wants."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.836,
                                "stop": 138.63,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Congress typically does that by speaking directly about a Court\u0027s power, not merely by setting time limits for litigants to follow."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.63,
                                "stop": 144.705,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "And today we hold that Congress did not restrict a Court\u0027s jurisdiction in the FTCA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 144.705,
                                "stop": 157.995,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Neither the text, nor the context, nor the legislative history of the FTCA provides a clear indication that Congress wanted the statute\u0027s time limits to operate as jurisdictional bars."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.995,
                                "stop": 164.358,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Those time limits look in every way like run-of-the-mill statutes of limitations, nothing more."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 164.358,
                                "stop": 174.866,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "They make clear when a claim is late, but they do not constrain a Court\u0027s power to adjudicate a late claim when there is very good reason to do so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 174.866,
                                "stop": 181.089,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That is what the Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit said below, so we affirm its judgments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 181.089,
                                "stop": 190.798,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has filed a dissenting opinion, in which the Chief Justice and Justices Scalia and Thomas join."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
